{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:john.10",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "john",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "John 10",
    "summary": "Source text for John 10 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:1",
      "text": "“Most certainly, I tell you, one who doesn’t enter by the door into the sheep fold, but climbs up some other way, is a thief and a robber.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:2",
      "text": "But one who enters in by the door is the shepherd of the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:3",
      "text": "The gatekeeper opens the gate for him, and the sheep listen to his voice. He calls his own sheep by name and leads them out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:4",
      "text": "Whenever he brings out his own sheep, he goes before them; and the sheep follow him, for they know his voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:5",
      "text": "They will by no means follow a stranger, but will flee from him; for they don’t know the voice of strangers.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:6",
      "text": "Jesus spoke this parable to them, but they didn’t understand what he was telling them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:7",
      "text": "Jesus therefore said to them again, “Most certainly, I tell you, I am the sheep’s door.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:8",
      "text": "All who came before me are thieves and robbers, but the sheep didn’t listen to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:9",
      "text": "I am the door. If anyone enters in by me, he will be saved, and will go in and go out and will find pasture.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:10",
      "text": "The thief only comes to steal, kill, and destroy. I came that they may have life, and may have it abundantly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:11",
      "text": "“I am the good shepherd. The good shepherd lays down his life for the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:12",
      "text": "He who is a hired hand, and not a shepherd, who doesn’t own the sheep, sees the wolf coming, leaves the sheep, and flees. The wolf snatches the sheep and scatters them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:13",
      "text": "The hired hand flees because he is a hired hand and doesn’t care for the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:14",
      "text": "I am the good shepherd. I know my own, and I’m known by my own;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:15",
      "text": "even as the Father knows me, and I know the Father. I lay down my life for the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:16",
      "text": "I have other sheep which are not of this fold. I must bring them also, and they will hear my voice. They will become one flock with one shepherd.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:17",
      "text": "Therefore the Father loves me, because I lay down my life, that I may take it again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:18",
      "text": "No one takes it away from me, but I lay it down by myself. I have power to lay it down, and I have power to take it again. I received this commandment from my Father.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:19",
      "text": "Therefore a division arose again among the Jews because of these words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:20",
      "text": "Many of them said, “He has a demon and is insane! Why do you listen to him?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:21",
      "text": "Others said, “These are not the sayings of one possessed by a demon. It isn’t possible for a demon to open the eyes of the blind, is it?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:22",
      "text": "It was the Feast of the Dedication at Jerusalem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:23",
      "text": "It was winter, and Jesus was walking in the temple, in Solomon’s porch.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:24",
      "text": "The Jews therefore came around him and said to him, “How long will you hold us in suspense? If you are the Christ, tell us plainly.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:25",
      "text": "Jesus answered them, “I told you, and you don’t believe. The works that I do in my Father’s name, these testify about me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:26",
      "text": "But you don’t believe, because you are not of my sheep, as I told you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:27",
      "text": "My sheep hear my voice, and I know them, and they follow me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:28",
      "text": "I give eternal life to them. They will never perish, and no one will snatch them out of my hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:29",
      "text": "My Father who has given them to me is greater than all. No one is able to snatch them out of my Father’s hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:30",
      "text": "I and the Father are one.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:31",
      "text": "Therefore the Jews took up stones again to stone him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:32",
      "text": "Jesus answered them, “I have shown you many good works from my Father. For which of those works do you stone me?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:33",
      "text": "The Jews answered him, “We don’t stone you for a good work, but for blasphemy, because you, being a man, make yourself God.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:34",
      "text": "Jesus answered them, “Isn’t it written in your law, ‘I said, you are gods ’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:35",
      "text": "If he called them gods, to whom the word of God came (and the Scripture can’t be broken),",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:36",
      "text": "do you say of him whom the Father sanctified and sent into the world, ‘You blaspheme,’ because I said, ‘I am the Son of God ’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:37",
      "text": "If I don’t do the works of my Father, don’t believe me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.38",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:38",
      "text": "But if I do them, though you don’t believe me, believe the works, that you may know and believe that the Father is in me, and I in the Father.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.39",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:39",
      "text": "They sought again to seize him, and he went out of their hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.40",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:40",
      "text": "He went away again beyond the Jordan into the place where John was baptizing at first, and he stayed there.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.41",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:41",
      "text": "Many came to him. They said, “John indeed did no sign, but everything that John said about this man is true.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:john.10.42",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:42",
      "text": "Many believed in him there.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
